				<wikidot:authorName>Decibelles</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2005044</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It <em>may</em> go on for too long, and the jokes get beaten into the ground a lot, but I think there's a lot of charm throughout. You two do an excellent job of characterizing everyone involved in the discussion (even the cameo appearances) and all the information given adds intrigue even if it isn't necessary at times. Plus, it's in one of my favorite formats ever. A really well-done job.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6128973#post-3834882</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6128973/the-sacred-djehuti#post-3834882</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 13 Jun 2018 23:10:10 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TL333s</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1304786</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Goddamn. :D I upvoted literally for the first two footnotes, but there's so much stuff going on here, I would have by the end anyway. (And tried to!)</p> <p>I've never seen the SPC dealt with in Serpents Hand format before. That was surreal. Also a little confusing, but then I haven't been too enamored with Team Bird's work to date, this being a major exception. Point being, I wouldn't be surprised if I missed something.</p> <p>I was also a little thrown by JV's working with the Foundation against Thoth. They proclaimed not to be a worshipper, but I wasn't expecting a full-on antagonist here.</p> <p>I like this, though, I really do. It's got a nice blend of serious and off-kilter, which is why I love SH formats to begin with. :)</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
